Executive showboating reached its ridiculous height the other day when state governors started meddling with higher education and rushing to rechristen polytechnics as universities. The arbitrariness of the me-too syndrome is symptomatic of a poor understanding of the difference between the two institutions and their unique relevance to Nigerian society. A country bedevilled by a high unemployment rate, yet yawning gap for skill-sets, needs more polytechnics, not universities, to bridge the gap.  